The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New York, Oct. 28 (PTI): A rally has been held in Philadelphia in protest against the Indian governments alleged failure to stop violence against Christians.           
	Despite numerous pleas for help, the Indian government has not sufficiently responded to the situation, said pamphlets distributed by the organisers, including representatives of local Indian churches.                  
	 Srinagar (PTI): Arrangements have been made for the departure of more than 8,000 Haj pilgrims from Jammu and Kashmir, a senior officer of the state Haj committee said on Tuesday. There will be daily flights from Srinagar to Saudi Arabia from October 30 till November 12 after which the frequency will be increased to two flights daily till November 25.                   
	 Kalpetta, Kerala (PTI): Twenty-two children from various communities, including the Scheduled Tribes, have been trained as temple priests by a Hindu group in Kalpetta in Kerala. The first batch of children who completed the 18-month training were authorised on Monday to perform pujas in temples.                  
	 Rameswaram (PTI): The coast guard arrested five Sri Lankan Tamils on Tuesday while they were heading to the Tamil Nadu coast in a boat. The men said they had fled Sri Lanka because of army operations against the LTTE near their localities.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Three youths from Ghaziabad and Muradabad in Uttar Pradesh have been arrested for their alleged involvement in the kidnap and murder of a Delhi-based businessman and his driver, police said. Ravi Jain and Gajraj, the driver, had gone missing on September 12.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): A night watchman was hacked to death at an industrial estate in Madurai in the early hours of Monday and lakhs of rupees kept in a cash box were stolen, police said.                                                                                                                          
